         <abstract>
            <p>Franco Modigliani and Richard Cohn's "Inflation, Rational Valuation and the Market" in the March/April 1979 issue of "Financial Analysts Journal" generated an extraordinary amount of interest and controversy. In the months subsequent to publication, the Journal received a number of unusually thoughtful letters. The best of these are published below, together with a reply from Modigliani and Cohn.</p>
          </abstract>
